<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="557" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1230,1866]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,518,1230,1255]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">Variation in wing pattern.</emphasis>
Although few specimens were available to us, some variation was observed. In males the coloration can be pure rose (
<collectingCountry box="[597,668,1266,1291]" name="Brazil" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) or have overtones of purple (
<collectingCountry box="[1018,1134,1266,1291]" name="Colombia" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">Colombia</collectingCountry>
), and the brown scale-less triangle below M 
<date box="[345,414,1303,1327]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">
<number box="[345,358,1303,1327]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" value="2.0">2</number>
may
</date>
be solid (brown bands amalgamated; 
<figureCitation box="[842,908,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURE 5. a – e, C" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1208,1230]" captionTargetBox="[159,1426,198,1159]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,191,1168]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 5. a – e, C. aurora; f, C. aurorina; g – i, C. pyritosa; dorsal view on the left, ventral on the right. Collecting localities and genitalia dissection codes appear below each specimen." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230844/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[894,908,1302,1327]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="5.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" unit="g" value="5.0">5</quantity>
</figureCitation>
g) or open (brown bands not amalgamated; 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 5. a – e, C" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1208,1230]" captionTargetBox="[159,1426,198,1159]" captionTargetId="figure@12.[151,1436,191,1168]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 5. a – e, C. aurora; f, C. aurorina; g – i, C. pyritosa; dorsal view on the left, ventral on the right. Collecting localities and genitalia dissection codes appear below each specimen." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230844/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">
Fig 
<number box="[151,165,1338,1363]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
h).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1230,1866]" box="[199,410,1374,1399]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1374,1399]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">Subspecies.</emphasis>
None.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="557" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1230,1866]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1410,1435]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">Remarks.</emphasis>
Although it is not possible to evaluate the length of the phallus and saccus from the original description of 
<taxonomicName box="[315,441,1447,1470]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Cithaerias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyritosa">
<emphasis box="[315,441,1447,1470]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">C. pyritosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on 
<typeStatus box="[564,612,1447,1471]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">type</typeStatus>
specimen photographs and localities, we concur with 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamas" box="[1228,1386,1447,1471]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" refString="Lamas, G. (1998) Lista sinonimica de los generos Cithaerias Hubner y Haetera Fabricius (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae: Satyrinae), con la descripcion de dos subespecies nuevas del Peru. Revista peruana de Entomologia, 40, 133 - 138." type="journal article" year="1998">
Lamas (
<number box="[1320,1378,1447,1471]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" value="1998.0">1998</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
that 
<taxonomicName box="[151,301,1482,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Cithaerias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similigena">
<emphasis box="[151,301,1482,1506]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">C. similigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler, 1868" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1868" box="[355,568,1482,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Callitaera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="pireta" subSpecies="amaryllis">
<emphasis box="[355,568,1482,1506]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">C. pireta amaryllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are synonyms of 
<taxonomicName box="[767,892,1482,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Cithaerias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyritosa">
<emphasis box="[767,892,1482,1506]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">C. pyritosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The male genitalia photograph of 
<taxonomicName box="[1286,1436,1482,1506]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Cithaerias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similigena">
<emphasis box="[1286,1436,1482,1506]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">C. similigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in D’Almeida (
<number box="[324,382,1518,1543]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" value="1951.0">1951</number>
) is quite similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[606,732,1519,1542]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Cithaerias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pyritosa">
<emphasis box="[606,732,1519,1542]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">C. pyritosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<figureCitation box="[771,838,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1319,1341]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,197,1277]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[158,1428,191,1287]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male genitalia in lateral and ventral views, tegument and uncus in dorsal view, and subscaphium in ventral view. Valva setae shown on one side only. When not clearly visible in the lateral view illustration, the phallus was shown separately. Given that the two parts of the subscaphium (subanal plate and adjacent sclerotized area) rest on the membranous diaphragma, the variation in the shape of the subanal plate includes preparation artifacts. Scale bar Scale bar 1 mm for all images. a, C. aurorina dissection CMP 13 - 13; b, C. pyritosa dissection CMP 14 - 04." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230846/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">
Fig. 
<number box="[824,838,1518,1543]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
b, but the phallus is proportionately longer. It is also important to note that the proportions of the male genitalia parts in lateral view illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Constantino" box="[1186,1402,1554,1579]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" refString="Constantino, L. M. (1995) Revision de la tribu Haeterini Herrich-Schaffer, 1864 en Colombia (Lepidoptera: Nymphalidae, Satyrinae). Shilap Revista de lepidopterologia, 23 (89), 49 - 76." type="journal article" year="1995">
Constantino (
<number box="[1336,1394,1554,1579]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
do not match those in D’Almeida (
<number box="[520,580,1590,1615]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" value="1951.0">1951</number>
; as 
<taxonomicName box="[627,780,1590,1614]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Cithaerias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="similigena">
<emphasis box="[627,780,1590,1614]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">C. similigena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) nor this study (
<figureCitation box="[975,1045,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1319,1341]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,197,1277]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[158,1428,191,1287]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male genitalia in lateral and ventral views, tegument and uncus in dorsal view, and subscaphium in ventral view. Valva setae shown on one side only. When not clearly visible in the lateral view illustration, the phallus was shown separately. Given that the two parts of the subscaphium (subanal plate and adjacent sclerotized area) rest on the membranous diaphragma, the variation in the shape of the subanal plate includes preparation artifacts. Scale bar Scale bar 1 mm for all images. a, C. aurorina dissection CMP 13 - 13; b, C. pyritosa dissection CMP 14 - 04." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/230846/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="557">
Fig. 
<number box="[1030,1045,1590,1615]" pageId="16" pageNumber="557" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
b). This variation warrants further examination.
</paragraph>
